  "prompt": "Is it actionable defamation to write online that you find someone to be a monster?",
  "response": "Whether a statement like calling someone a \"monster\" constitutes legally actionable defamation depends on several factors:\n\n1. Context matters greatly\n2. The statement would need to be:\n- A demonstrably false statement of fact\n- Published/communicated to others\n- Causing actual harm to the person's reputation\n- Made with negligence or malice\n\nSimply expressing an opinion (\"I think they're a monster\") is typically protected speech. Specific, factual accusations suggesting criminal or unethical behavior could potentially be defamatory.\n\nFor a definitive legal assessment, consulting a local attorney specializing in defamation law would be recommended.",
